Job Description:
Key Account Manager Chemicals

Job Description

I. IDENTIFICATION

Supervisor: Sales Manager Date Completed: 07/27/2020

Department: Possehl Erzkontor North America FLSA Classification: Exempt

Location(s): Cincinnati, OH, or remote Status: Full-Time

II. PRINCIPAL ACCOUNTABILITIES (SUMMARY)

Reporting directly to the Sales Manager, the Key Account Manager for Chemicals is a sales role focusing on selling to domestic Chemical Market as well as supporting a global export business. Experience in the industrial chemical market with established contacts and business is needed, as well as leadership qualities to support the existing sales team.

Key Account Manager for Chemicals will be fully supported by international purchasing and supply chain team in the daily business.

III. POSITION REQUIREMENTS

Education, Credentials, Licenses:
B.A. or B.S degree in a Business-related discipline or equivalent combination of experience and education.

Kind & Length of Experience:
Minimum 5 years of demonstrated experience in an chemicals sales focused role with emphasis on order fulfillment and customer satisfaction.
Excellent organizational skills and able to handle multiple priorities
Effective written and verbal communication skills
Flexible and able to change direction as needed or requested
Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) data entry or system experience
Efficient with computer skills and Microsoft Office products
Able to meet deadlines
IV. PERFORMANCE MEASURES AND STANDARDS
New Customers opened
Top Line, Profitability, Gross Margin
Understand specific customer requirements;
Communicate effectively both externally and internally;
Accurate and timely prepare Purchase Orders, Sales Orders, and Invoices;
Analyze or produce reports for business leaders and others;
Ensure orders invoiced within 24 hours of shipment and receipts entered within 24 hours of activity;
In your absence, you are to ensure that the tasks assigned to you are adequately covered by trained personnel. You are responsible to communicate and work with your manager to ensure your workload is covered when you are out.
Other duties and assigned.
Possehl Erzkontor Training Required
We will follow the company written training program for this position.
Customer Service, Teamwork & Code of Conduct
Maintain a safe, legal and environmentally protective operation;
Listen to our customers, suppliers and employees;
Respond quickly to customer concerns;
Follow set guidelines for GMP, quality and food safety requirements;
Maintain training on applicable procedures in quality, GMP, and food safety;
Report any food safety, security, and / or quality issues to management or the HACCP team to initiate action;
Provide flexible and innovative strategies to support new business opportunities;
Be cost effective in the utilization of our resources, thereby contributing to the profitability of Possehl Erzkontor North America INC and our customers;
Strive for continued improvement;
Willing and eagerness to learn;
Maintain positive Can Do attitude.

