Our work at ISU Insurance Services of Colorado starts with empathy – truly understanding what our clients and prospects want and need to be successful in their endeavors. The ability to translate insurance into something others, not in our industry, can understand is a must.

Since 1882, ISU Insurance has had a consistent mission – we provide insurance products and services to enable clients to be in control of their future security. Our trusted staff has the knowledge and experience to provide maximum benefit and protection to our clients.

Our current openings are for a *_Commercial Property & Casualty Account Manager_* in our Commercial Lines division.

ISU’s work environment is fast paced, positive, and results-oriented. We offer excellent employee benefits, including Medical, Short and Long Term Disability, Life Insurance, Long Term Care and 401(k). We also enjoy business casual attire and reasonably flexible working hours.

If you’re interested in this position, please provide a brief cover letter describing your related experience and skills, along with your resume, via Indeed.com. We look forward to hearing from you!

\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_
Job Summary*
The Property & Casualty Commercial Lines Account Manager is responsible for the delivery of services, with an emphasis on Commercial Product Lines. This position contributes to the Agency’s growth and profitability through excellence in quality service and sales to existing and new accounts.

Our goal with every client is to provide a consistent response when serving their personal, professional, and business needs. As a member of our team, the Commercial Lines Account Manager is expected to contribute to this goal with a focus on problem solving, customer satisfaction, and personal accountability.
Primary Job Responsibilities*
Understand and serve ISU client needs via email and phone;
Handle claims, including reporting and follow up;
Organize and prioritize work, tracking deadlines;
Conduct client contract analysis;
Coordinate requests for additional information between the client and the Carriers;
Process policies and endorsements, including changes;
Ensure the accuracy and completeness of policy and endorsement submissions;
Work with Producer to manage expiration process (marketing through policy delivery);
Ensure receipt of money from clients in advance of binding insurance, as relates to Specialty markets;
Develop, maintain, and deliver Professional Proposals and Summaries of Insurance;
Perform Agency invoicing and billing procedures;
Respond to requests for information related to client audit procedures;
Understand Carrier rating systems; participate in Carrier meetings;
Collect, organize, and communicate monthly client data;
Comply with all safety policies, practices, and procedures. Report all unsafe activities to supervisor;
Provide, and be open to, constructive feedback to continually improve our client experience and our internal efficiency;
Participate in proactive team efforts to achieve departmental and company goals, and to improve policies and procedures;
Minimal overnight travel; and
Perform other duties as assigned.
Knowledge and Skills*
Broad knowledge of Commercial Product Lines;
Working knowledge of Certificates of Insurance;
Knowledge of Surety Bonding;
Knowledge of Insurance carrier markets and how to block markets;
Strong written, verbal, and active listening communication skills;
Skilled in electronic mail and Microsoft Office Suite, with focus on Word and Excel for use in developing Professional Proposals, Summaries of Insurance, and routine reporting of data;
Knowledge of AMS or other Agency Management Systems; ability to navigate Premium Finance Company Computer sites;
Demonstrated self-starter who works independently, possesses good common sense, and takes personal accountability for outcomes;
Good organizational, problem solving, and time management skills;
Work in a semi-paperless environment;
Operate within specific company guidelines and delegate work as needed;
Demonstrated aptitude for numbers and data analysis;
Flexible, present and focused during working hours; able to handle occasional stress, and
Promote teamwork through example and sharing of knowledge/skills.
Education and Experience*
Bachelor's degree in business or related coursework is desirable;
3-5 years of related experience and/or training in the insurance industry;
An equivalent combination of experience and education related to the position will be considered;
Property & Casualty License and Life & Health License is preferred; and
CIC or CPCU designations are a plus.
Essential Job Functions*
Manual dexterity sufficient to reach and handle items with fingers, hands, and arms;
Ability to sit for extended periods of time at computer;
Ability to speak, read, write, see, hear, and communicate clearly;
Ability to have clear vision at 20 inches or less, distance vision at 20 feet or more, identify and distinguish colors, and perceive attributes of objects and materials;
Lift up to 10 pounds; and
Perform and complete multiple tasks.
Job Type: Full-time

